**'Ehd-e-Tifli'** is chapter 19 of Bang-e-Dara Part 1 (`allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-1-55b25c`). The poem recalls childhood wonder — the earth and sky as a new world, the mother's lap as a universe, joy in the rattle of a door-chain, and hours spent staring at the moon with endless questions. It ends with the striking couplet: *"It was no heart I had, but pure, inquiring thought"* — the child as pure inquiry before the heart takes over.
